From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: drm/bridge: simple: add the Chrontel CH7218A DP-to-HDMI bridge

The Q8B routes HDMI through a Chrontel CH7218A, a transparent DP-to-HDMI
bridge with compatible "chrontel,ch7218a". It has no entry in
simple_bridge_match, so the driver never probes and the board has no HDMI
output. Add it as an HDMI-A connector alongside the other transparent
DP-to-HDMI bridges.

Original work by Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>, rebased onto v7.1.

Signed-off-by: SuperKali <hello@superkali.me>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/simple-bridge.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/simple-bridge.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/simple-bridge.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/simple-bridge.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/bridge/simple-bridge.c
@@ -270,6 +270,11 @@ static const struct of_device_id simple_bridge_match[] = {
 		.data = &(const struct simple_bridge_info) {
 			.connector_type = DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_HDMIA,
 		},
+	}, {
+		.compatible = "chrontel,ch7218a",
+		.data = &(const struct simple_bridge_info) {
+			.connector_type = DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_HDMIA,
+		},
 	}, {
 		.compatible = "parade,ps185hdm",
 		.data = &(const struct simple_bridge_info) {
-- 
Armbian

